net.openhft.chronicle.core.util

Interface ThrowingBiConsumer<I,J,T extends Throwable>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of the input to the function
    T - the type of Throwable thrown
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ThrowingBiConsumer<I,J,T extends Throwable>
    Represents an operation that accepts two input arguments and returns no result. Unlike most other functional interfaces, ThrowingBiConsumer is expected to operate via side-effects.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is accept(Object, Object).
